			</a>
		</div>
	</nav>

	<section class="page-header">
		<h1>Run it <span class="accent">for real</span></h1>
		<p class="subtitle">You've followed the Get Started guide and it works locally. Now you want it running 24/7, handling real webhooks, on real repos. Here's how.</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Production checklist</h2>
		<div class="checklist">
			<div class="check-item">
				<span class="check-icon">1</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Pick a host</h3>
					<p>Last Light needs a long-running process with a public URL for webhooks. Good options:</p>
					<div class="options-grid">
						<div class="option-card">
							<h4>VPS / Dedicated</h4>
							<p>Any Linux box works. Run inside <code>tmux</code> or use <code>systemd</code>. Cheapest option — a $5/mo VPS handles dozens of repos.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="option-card">
							<h4>Docker</h4>
							<p>Use the built-in Docker backend for isolation. Mount your <code>.env</code> and private key. Works on any container host.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="option-card">
							<h4>Modal (recommended)</h4>
							<p>Cloud sandbox with auto-scaling. The terminal runs in Modal VMs while the agent runs on your host. Best isolation with zero container management.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="check-item">
				<span class="check-icon">2</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Expose webhooks</h3>
					<p>GitHub needs to reach your webhook endpoint. The default is <code>http://your-host:8644/webhooks/github</code>.</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Public server:</strong> Open port 8644, or reverse-proxy through nginx/Caddy with TLS.</li>
						<li><strong>Behind NAT:</strong> Use <a href="https://ngrok.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ngrok</a>, <a href="https://developers.cloudflare.com/cloudflare-one/connections/connect-apps/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cloudflare Tunnel</a>, or <a href="https://tailscale.com/kb/1223/funnel" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tailscale Funnel</a> to get a public URL.</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="section-note">Set your webhook URL in the GitHub App settings, and the same secret in both places (<code>WEBHOOK_SECRET</code> in <code>.env</code>, and the GitHub App webhook config).</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="check-item">
				<span class="check-icon">3</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Secure your secrets</h3>
					<p>Your <code>.env</code> contains API keys and your GitHub App private key. In production:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Restrict file permissions: <code>chmod 600 .env *.pem</code></li>
						<li>Don't commit secrets — both are in <code>.gitignore</code> by default</li>
						<li>Consider a secrets manager (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, etc.) for team deployments</li>
						<li>The GitHub App private key is the most sensitive asset — it can act as your bot on any installed repo</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="check-item">
				<span class="check-icon">4</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Install the GitHub App on your repos</h3>
					<p>Go to your GitHub App's settings page and install it on the repos (or org) you want Last Light to manage. The bot only sees repos where it's installed.</p>
					<p>Required permissions: Issues (read/write), Pull Requests (read/write), Contents (read/write), Metadata (read).</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="check-item">
				<span class="check-icon">5</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Start the gateway</h3>
					<p>For production, run the gateway (not interactive CLI):</p>
					<pre><code>./lastlight gateway</code></pre>
					<p>This starts the webhook listener, Discord bot (if configured), and cron scheduler. To keep it running:</p>
					<pre><code># With systemd (recommended)
sudo systemctl enable lastlight
sudo systemctl start lastlight

# Or with tmux
tmux new -s lastlight './lastlight gateway'

# Or with Docker
docker compose up -d</code></pre>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="check-item">
				<span class="check-icon">6</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Verify it's working</h3>
					<p>Open an issue on one of your installed repos. Last Light should triage it within seconds (webhooks) or minutes (cron). Check:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Labels were applied</li>
						<li>The bot left a triage comment</li>
						<li>Logs show the event was received: <code>tail -f logs/</code></li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Operational tips</h2>
		<div class="tips-grid">
			<div class="tip-card">
				<h3>Token refresh</h3>
				<p>GitHub App tokens expire hourly. The MCP server handles this automatically — no action needed. If you see auth errors in logs, restart the agent to force a fresh token.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="tip-card">
				<h3>Rate limits</h3>
				<p>GitHub App installations get 5,000 API calls/hour. For most repos that's plenty. If you hit limits, increase the cron interval or reduce the number of repos per installation.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="tip-card">
				<h3>LLM costs</h3>
				<p>Each issue triage or PR review is one LLM call. At typical usage (a few events/day), costs are minimal. Set a fallback model in <code>config.yaml</code> to avoid downtime when your primary provider rate-limits.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="tip-card">
				<h3>Logs & debugging</h3>
				<p>Session logs are saved to <code>logs/</code> as JSON trajectories. Each webhook event gets its own session file. Use these to debug unexpected behavior or replay events.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="tip-card">
				<h3>Multiple repos</h3>
				<p>One Last Light instance handles all repos where the GitHub App is installed. No per-repo configuration needed — skills apply universally. Customize behavior by editing the skill files.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="tip-card">
				<h3>Updating</h3>
				<p>Pull the latest from the repo and restart. Hermes itself updates separately via <code>hermes update</code>. Skills are versioned — check the changelog for breaking changes.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Example: systemd service</h2>
		<p class="section-desc">A minimal systemd unit file to keep Last Light running on a Linux server.</p>
		<pre><code>[Unit]
Description=Last Light GitHub Agent
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=lastlight
WorkingDirectory=/opt/lastlight
ExecStart=/opt/lastlight/lastlight gateway
Restart=on-failure
RestartSec=10
Environment=HOME=/opt/lastlight

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target</code></pre>
	</section>

	<footer>
		<div class="footer-content">
			<img src="/logo.png" alt="Last Light" width="32" height="32" />
			<div class="footer-links">
				<a href="/">Home</a>
				<span class="footer-sep">/</span>
				<a href="/run-it">Run It for Real</a>
				<span class="footer-sep">/</span>
				<a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
				<span class="footer-sep">/</span>
				<a href="https://github.com/users/cliftonc/projects/4" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Roadmap</a>
				<span class="footer-sep">/</span>
				<a href="https://github.com/cliftonc/lastlight" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a>
			</div>
			<p class="footer-meta">MIT License. Built with <a href="https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hermes Agent</a>.</p>
		</div>
	</footer>

</body>
</html>

<style is:global>
	:root {
		--gold: #F0B429;
		--orange: #E8752A;
		--teal: #1A7A8A;
		--teal-dark: #135E6B;
		--navy: #1B2735;
		--bg: #0C1117;
		--bg-card: #141B24;
		--bg-card-hover: #1A2332;
		--border: #1E2A38;
		--text: #C9D1D9;
		--text-muted: #7D8694;
		--text-bright: #ECEFF4;
		--mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
		--sans: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
	}

	* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
	html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

	body {
		background: var(--bg);
		color: var(--text);
		font-family: var(--sans);
		line-height: 1.6;
		-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
	}

	a { color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.2s; }
	a:hover { color: var(--orange); }
	h1, h2, h3 { color: var(--text-bright); font-weight: 600; }

	code {
		font-family: var(--mono);
		font-size: 0.85em;
		background: var(--navy);
		padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
		border-radius: 4px;
		color: var(--gold);
	}

	pre {
		background: var(--navy);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 8px;
		padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
		overflow-x: auto;
		margin: 0.75rem 0;
	}

	pre code {
		background: none;
		padding: 0;
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		color: var(--text);
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	nav {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: center;
		padding: 1.25rem 2rem;
		max-width: 1100px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.nav-logo {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.6rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--text-bright);
		font-size: 1rem;
	}

	.nav-logo:hover { color: var(--gold); }

	.nav-links {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1.25rem;
	}

	.nav-links a {
		color: var(--text-muted);
		font-size: 0.88rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		transition: color 0.2s;
	}

	.nav-links a:hover { color: var(--text-bright); }

	.gh-link {
		color: var(--text-muted);
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		padding: 0.4rem;
		border-radius: 6px;
		transition: color 0.2s, background 0.2s;
	}

	.gh-link:hover {
		color: var(--text-bright);
		background: var(--bg-card);
	}

	section {
		max-width: 1000px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 3rem 2rem;
	}

	section h2 {
		font-size: 1.6rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
	}

	.accent { color: var(--gold); }

	.section-desc {
		color: var(--text-muted);
		max-width: 600px;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		line-height: 1.65;
	}

	.section-note {
		background: var(--bg-card);
		border-left: 3px solid var(--teal);
		padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
		border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
		font-size: 0.88rem;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		margin-top: 0.75rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	/* Page header */
	.page-header {
		max-width: 1000px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 4rem 2rem 1rem;
	}

	.page-header h1 {
		font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.page-header .subtitle {
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		max-width: 600px;
		line-height: 1.65;
	}

	/* Checklist */
	.checklist {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 2rem;
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
	}

	.check-item {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1.25rem;
		align-items: flex-start;
	}

	.check-icon {
		flex-shrink: 0;
		width: 32px;
		height: 32px;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		border-radius: 50%;
		background: var(--teal);
		color: var(--text-bright);
		font-weight: 600;
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		font-family: var(--mono);
	}

	.check-item h3 {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
	}

	.check-item p {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.check-item ul {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0.5rem 0;
	}

	.check-item ul li {
		font-size: 0.88rem;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		line-height: 1.65;
		padding-left: 1.25rem;
		position: relative;
	}

	.check-item ul li::before {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		top: 0.55em;
		width: 6px;
		height: 6px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		background: var(--teal);
	}

	/* Options grid */
	.options-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 0.75rem;
		margin-top: 0.75rem;
	}

	.option-card {
		background: var(--bg-card);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 10px;
		padding: 1.25rem;
		transition: border-color 0.25s;
	}

	.option-card:hover {
		border-color: #2A3A4D;
	}

	.option-card h4 {
		color: var(--text-bright);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
	}

	.option-card p {
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		line-height: 1.55;
	}

	/* Tips grid */
	.tips-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-top: 1.25rem;
	}

	.tip-card {
		background: var(--bg-card);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 10px;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		transition: border-color 0.25s, background 0.25s;
	}

	.tip-card:hover {
		border-color: #2A3A4D;
		background: var(--bg-card-hover);
	}

	.tip-card h3 {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
	}

	.tip-card p {
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	/* Footer */
	footer {
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
		padding: 2rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}

	.footer-content {
		max-width: 1000px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.75rem;
	}

	.footer-links {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		font-size: 0.82rem;
	}

	.footer-links a {
		color: var(--text-muted);
		transition: color 0.2s;
	}

	.footer-links a:hover {
		color: var(--gold);
	}

	.footer-sep {
		color: var(--border);
		font-size: 0.75rem;
	}

	.footer-meta {
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		margin-left: auto;
	}

	.footer-content p {
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		color: var(--text-muted);
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.options-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
		.tips-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
		.nav-links { gap: 0.75rem; }
		.nav-links a { font-size: 0.8rem; }
		.footer-content { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
		.footer-meta { margin-left: 0; }
	}
</style>
